(1, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '6', 'NOUN Tma Solutions App', 'Noun TMA Solution - Apps on Google Play', '231806154732000000download.jpg', 'noun-tma-solution-apps-on-google-play', '<h1 style=\"text-align:right\"><strong>National Open University, NOUN TMA Solution Application</strong></h1>\n\n<p>Welcome to our NOUN Tma Solution Web App - Live Answers. Our Noun TMA Solution Application is specifically designed for ALL (100Level-800Level) students of National Open University of Nigeria to solve their TMA at ease without stress.</p>\n\n<p>This TMA Web Application is for self submission and can be used by both students and NOUN agents.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s NOT auto, rather manual application. It&rsquo;s very simple, you only input the question on the search button and automatically it will take you to the location of the answer. With this App, atleast 80% of all your TMAs will be solved/submitted with GOOD SCORES!</p>\n\n<p>This App was created to benefit the academic life of NOUN students and for them to do everything at ease.</p>\n\n<p>Thus, it&rsquo;s important to know that Tutor Marked Assignment (TMA) is a marking scheme for NOUN, and it contributes 30% of the student total mark. This Applies to all students/Programmes be it a First Degree, Postgraduate Diploma, Masters&rsquo;s Degree</p>\n\n<p>Tutor Marked Assignments (TMAs) play a significant role in enhancing a student&#39;s learning skills and helping them become a meritorious learner.</p>\n\n<p>The GOOD NEWS is that with our NOUN TMA Solution Application, you can easily submit all your Tmas on time and with EASE!</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/student-registeration\">SIGNUP NOW!</a></p>\n', '2023-06-18 19:47:32', '2023-06-18 19:47:32'),
(3, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '3', 'NOUN E exams Past Questions and Answers', 'NOUN PAST QUESTIONS', '231806160627000000PQ.jpg', 'noun-past-questions', '<p>ALL NOUN PAST QUESTIONS ARE CURRENTLY AVAILABLE</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;NOUN Past Question are usually&nbsp;dynamic i.e they do repeats their exam questions from previous</p>\n\n<p>years. Don&rsquo;t be surprised to see questions of 2023 in this&nbsp;year examination.</p>\n\n<p>That simply means thatfor you to&nbsp;fortified and come out successfully with good grades&nbsp;you must be acquainted with PastQuestions.</p>\n\n<p>1: E-Exam PAST QUESTIONS now Available</p>\n\n<p>2: POP Exam PAST QUESTIONS now Available (Year:2018- 2023)</p>\n\n<p>WE HAVE NOUN PAST QUESTIONS ON&nbsp;THE FOLLOWING FACULTY:</p>\n\n<p>Entrepreneurship And General Studies</p>\n\n<p>Agricultural Sciences</p>\n\n<p>Arts</p>\n\n<p>Education</p>\n\n<p>Health Sciences</p>\n\n<p>Law</p>\n\n<p>Management&nbsp;Sciences</p>\n\n<p>Sciences</p>\n\n<p>Social Sciences</p>\n\n<p>Postgraduate School</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\">DOWNLOAD: NOUN Past Questions</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://html.scribdassets.com/azcm5303k7cee1v/images/1-26df61e4b7.jpg\" /></p>\n', '2023-06-18 20:06:27', '2023-06-18 20:06:27'),
(4, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '7', 'NOUN Tma Portal', 'How to Take NOUN TMA (Tutor Marked Assignment)', '2318061614160000002.png', 'how-to-take-noun-tma-tutor-marked-assignment', '<p><strong>&ndash; National Open University Of Nigeria (NOUN) TMA Portal has been CHANGED!</strong></p>\n\n<p>&ndash;&nbsp;<strong>Procedures to follow on how to Take NOUN TMA has been modefied</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&ndash; When you log in as a student you are taken straight to the TMA Portal page where your registered exams are listed. Click on the appropriate TMA and start answering.</strong></p>\n\n<h2>National Open University of Nigeria TMA Explained</h2>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/student/tma-search\">Tutor Marked Assignment (TMA)</a>&nbsp;is a marking scheme for NOUN, and it contributes 30% of the student total mark. Point to Note, this same as Test in other learning institutions.</p>\n\n<p>The Student is expected to answer or submit Three (3) NOUN TMA. Then, her Best three solved TMAs will be selected and marked by 30%.</p>\n\n<p>The Assignment is to be done at your pace and convince in as much as you don&rsquo;t exceed the giving time (deadline) for submission because it has a closing date.</p>\n\n<p>Then,&nbsp;the final examination&nbsp;takes 70% score mark hence, making TMAs necessary if a student must come out with a&nbsp;more excellent result.</p>\n\n<p>Want to access your Tutor-marked assignments TMA Portal? To begin TMA submission?&nbsp; Follow the procedures below.</p>\n\n<h2><strong>HOW TO TAKE TMA ON NOUN PORTAL</strong></h2>\n\n<p>1. Go to the&nbsp;<strong>National Open University Of Nigeria NOUN</strong>&nbsp;website &gt;&nbsp;www.nouonline.net</p>\n\n<p>2. Click on&nbsp;&ldquo;<strong>STUDENT&rdquo;,&nbsp;</strong>click on<strong>&nbsp;&ldquo;Log in&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;Nouonline Portal Login Page, enter your&nbsp;<strong>matric number</strong>, &nbsp;<strong>password</strong>&nbsp;and click the&nbsp;&ldquo;<strong>S</strong><strong>ubmit</strong>&ldquo;&nbsp;button.</p>\n\n<p>Now you should be on your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\">Nouonline student profile</a>&nbsp;page.</p>\n\n<p>3. In the&nbsp;NOUN&nbsp;studware&nbsp;menu options. Click on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/student/tma-search\">&ldquo;2023/2 TMA &ldquo;</a></strong>&nbsp;(You will be asked to log in again, enter your&nbsp;<strong>matric number</strong>, &nbsp;<strong>password</strong>&nbsp;and click the&nbsp;&ldquo;<strong>S</strong><strong>ubmit</strong>&ldquo;&nbsp;button)</p>\n\n<p>Cool, you&rsquo;re &nbsp;now at the&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\">NOUN TMA Portal PAGE</a>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n<p>4. Scroll down and click on&nbsp;<strong>TAKE TMA 1, TMA 2 OR TMA 3</strong></p>\n\n<p>7. TMA is on the right side of the page.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n', '2023-06-18 20:14:16', '2023-06-18 20:14:16'),
(5, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '5', 'NOUN Tma Solutions', 'Download Noun Tma Solution', '231806162028000000download.jpg', 'download-noun-tma-solution', '<h2 style=\"text-align:center\">NOUN TMA SOLUTION CENTRE</h2>\n\n<p>Welcome to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\">Nounloaded Tma Application </a>Solution Centre!</strong>&nbsp;We Provides Solutions to the National Open University Of Nigeria NOUN TMA Questions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Nounloaded TMA Web App is&nbsp;</strong>dedicated to providing Answers and Solutions to all the National Open University Of Nigeria Tutor Marked Assessment Questions Irrespective of the Student&rsquo;s Course, Level, or Programme of Study.</p>\n\n<p>Every fully registered NOUN University student knows that TMA constitutes 30% of your total course Grade and if you are guaranteed to have those 30 Marks in each of your courses, you now have greater chances of passing that course no matter how difficult it is and also the chances of carrying that course would be greatly reduced. This Applies to all NOUN Programmes be it a First Degree, Postgraduate Diploma, Masters&rsquo;s Degree</p>\n\n<p>Having high marks in your Tutor Marked Assessment Tests is very crucial to scoring good grades in your courses. For Instance, with<strong>&nbsp;30 marks in TMA</strong>, having an A in a course only requires you to have at least 40 Marks in the Exams while to have a Pass or Credit, you only need to score at least 20 Marks in the Exam.&nbsp;<strong>The Importance of high TMA Marks cannot be overemphasized.</strong></p>\n\n<p>The prices for our TMA Answers vary with the program of study because of the Increasing level of Question Ambiguity for higher Programs of Study. Our Price is cheap and affordable for all&nbsp;students.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/student/tma-live\">NOUN TMA LIVE ANSWERS</a></p>\n', '2023-06-18 20:20:28', '2023-06-18 20:20:28'),
(6, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '6', 'NOUN Tma Solutions App', 'NOUN TMA SOLVER (National Open University)', '2318061623450000002.png', 'noun-tma-solver-national-open-university', '<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">NOUN TMA SOLVER</h1>\n\n<p>This TMA Web Application is for self submission and can be used by both students and NOUN agents.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s NOT auto, rather manual application. It&rsquo;s very simple, you only input the question on the search button and automatically it will take you to the location of the answer. With this App, atleast 80% of all your TMAs will be solved/submitted with GOOD SCORES!</p>\n\n<p>This App was created to benefit the academic life of NOUN students and for them to do everything at ease.</p>\n\n<p>Thus, it&rsquo;s important to know that Tutor Marked Assignment (TMA) is a marking scheme for NOUN, and it contributes 30% of the student total mark. This Applies to all students/Programmes be it a First Degree, Postgraduate Diploma, Masters&rsquo;s Degree</p>\n\n<p>Tutor Marked Assignments (TMAs) play a significant role in enhancing a student&#39;s learning skills and helping them become a meritorious learner.</p>\n\n<p>The GOOD NEWS is that with our NOUN TMA Solution Application, you can easily submit all your Tmas on time and with EASE!</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/student-registeration\">SIGNUP NOW!</a></p>\n', '2023-06-18 20:23:45', '2023-06-18 20:23:45'),
(7, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'NOUN Admission Requirements', '231906105743000000admission2.jpg', 'noun-admission-requirements', '<h1>Step by Step Procedure on How to Apply for Admission</h1>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Visit the site&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng\">www.nouonline.net</a></li>\n	<li>On the Home Page, go to the Menu Bar, Click on Apply for Admission</li>\n	<li>Select either Undergraduate Programme or Postgraduate Programme. Other programme is not available at the moment</li>\n	<li>Goto &ldquo;Choose Faculty&rdquo; (note it can be found at the left hand side of the screen)</li>\n	<li>Select Faculty</li>\n	<li>Fill displayed form</li>\n	<li>Click below to view admission criteria</li>\n	<li>Click &ldquo;Apply&rdquo; to proceed.</li>\n	<li>Take note of the UNIQUE ID displayed</li>\n	<li>Click &lsquo;Continue&rsquo; button</li>\n	<li>Select Bank Branch as payment type</li>\n	<li>Click &ldquo;Pay&rdquo;</li>\n	<li>Copy and take your RRR number to any bank branch for payment.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>After payment</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Perform step 1 to 3</li>\n	<li>Goto &ldquo;Continue After Payment&rdquo;</li>\n	<li>Input Unique ID, RRR number and Programme</li>\n	<li>Click &ldquo;Proceed&rdquo;</li>\n	<li>Fill Form.&nbsp; Note: all fields marked with red star are compulsory.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>After filling form</strong></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Click &ldquo;Submit&rdquo;</li>\n	<li>Print Admission Letter</li>\n	<li>Visit the nearest study centre for screening</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>For Admission assistance, <a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\">CLICK HERE</a></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Studying with us gives a rewarding experience as we give you all the support you need to succeed.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Undergraduate Programmes</strong></h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>An applicant for undergraduate admission into NOUN is normally expected to have a minimum of 5 O-level credits including English Language and Mathematics.</li>\n	<li>Additional requirements might apply for some programmes and these can be viewed after selecting the Programme and entry level at the Faculty&rsquo;s admission page.</li>\n	<li>To apply for a programme, select the Faculty, choose the programme and entry level so that the&nbsp;<em>View Requirement</em>&nbsp;button is enabled. Clicking this button will reveal the corresponding entry requirement and enable the&nbsp;<em>Apply</em>&nbsp;button on the pre-payment application page.</li>\n	<li>Fill in all the remaining details on the page before submitting.</li>\n	<li>On successful submission of the pre-payment form, you are redirected to Remita to obtain an RRR invoice which should be used to effect payment for the application form.</li>\n	<li>An applicant who pays online using a payment card will automatically obtain the online form which must be filled before submission.</li>\n	<li>Applicants who pay through a bank branch must click on &ldquo;Continue After Payment&rdquo; and enter their Unique ID and RRR. They are also given the opportunity to change the Programme applied for.</li>\n	<li>Applicants who had paid using an RRR generated last semester or earlier must restart the application process upto the point when they are re-directed to remita. They should now use the newly generated UniqueID with the old RRR used for payment when they click&nbsp;<em>Proceed after payment</em>.</li>\n	<li>In all cases a successful payment will lead to the generation of an online application form which should be filled before submission online. The admission process is automated and the outcome is virtually instantaneous!</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>Postgraduate Programmes</strong></h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>To qualify for admission into any of the postgraduate programmes of the University, a candidate must meet, among others, all matriculation requirements of at least five (5) credit passes including English Language and Mathematics. Some programmes accept at least a pass in Mathematics.</li>\n	<li>For Postgraduate Diploma Programmes, Candidates must possess either a minimum of pass Bachelors Degree in any discipline from a University recognised by the Senate of the NOUN OR a Higher National Diploma with a minimum of Lower Credit. For the Postgraduate Diploma in Legislative Drafting, the candidate must have been called to the Bar. Also for admission into the school of Business and Human Resource Management Postgraduate Diploma programmes, candidates with professional qualifications such as ACA, ACIS, ACIB, ACII, ACIA, etc may be considered on individual merit.</li>\n	<li>For Master degree programmes, candidates must possess either a Bachelors Degree with a minimum of second class lower in the relevant field of study from a University recongnised by the Senate of the NOUN. However, holders of lower classification and with a minimum of 2 years of relevant post-qualification experience may be considered on individual merit OR a Postgraduate Diploma in related field of study from a recongnised University OR A Higher National Diploma with a minimum of Upper Credit in the relevant field of study. Candidate with membership certificate of relevant professional bodies may apply for the Master of Business (MBA) programme.</li>\n	<li>For the Doctor of Philosophy Degree prorammes, candidates must possess a masters degree in relevant field of study from a University recongised by the Senate of the NOUN with a minimum score average of not less than 60% or a cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) of 3.5 on a 5-point scale.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>You are welcome.</p>\n', '2023-06-19 14:57:43', '2023-06-19 14:57:43'),
(9, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'NOUN 2023/2024 Admission: National Open University of Nigeria Admission Requirements', '231906110807000000admission.png', 'noun-20232024-admission-national-open-university-of-nigeria-admission-requirements', '<p>Seeking for more information on how to get admission into NOUN? Don&rsquo;t worry, because we have here with us, the NOUN 2023/2024 Admission document, which lists out all the admission requirements for NOUN different course:</p>\n\n<h2><strong>Here&rsquo;s the National Open University of Nigeria Admission Requirements:</strong></h2>\n\n<p>Using this platform, the nounloaded.com.ng&nbsp;team, wishes to notify all potential and aspiring candidates of the National Open University of Nigeria, that the 2023/2024 admission application form into the academic institution has been released and it&rsquo;s out.</p>\n\n<p>The nounloaded.com.ng&nbsp;team, wishes to notify Members of the general public, especially, all interested candidates, who are seeking for admission into the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN), that the application Form for 2023/2024 Admission is now ongoing and you can join the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/posts/noun-admission-requirements-admission-application-and-registration-form/\">registration</a>.</p>\n\n<p>All interested applicants, should note, that the sales of NOUN Admission form for the 2023/2024 admission has been opened, which was also confirmed by the management of the academic institution.</p>\n\n<p>Before seeking for admission, here are the requirements you should take Note of.</p>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements into NOUN For Under Graduates</h3>\n\n<p>Seeking for admission into NOUN as an Under graduates? Here are the NOUN official requirements:</p>\n\n<p>1. You are required to score up to five (5) credits in the SSCE/GCE O&rsquo;Level/NECO/NABTEB or equivalents at not more than two (2) sittings, which you must have obtained in subjects which are relevant to the proposed field(s) of study.</p>\n\n<p>2. Applicants should take note, that the &ldquo;Teachers&rsquo; Grade II Certificate with a minimum of five merits or its combination with any of the certificates listed under (1) to obtain equivalent of five credits at &lsquo;O&rsquo; levels.</p>\n\n<p>3. We would also love to inform all candidates, who are currently seeking for admission into the NOUN School of Law, that they must have up to five (5) credits, which must include the following subjects:<br />\nEnglish Language,<br />\nLiterature in English,<br />\nAt least a credit Pass in Mathematics at not more than two (2) sittings in.</p>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements into NOUN For 200 LEVEL (For Direct Entry)</h3>\n\n<p>Here&rsquo;s the NOUN management board requirements for direct Entry Admission.</p>\n\n<p>i. You must have a National Diploma, which should come from a recognized institutions in Nigeria.</p>\n\n<p>ii. You are also required to have a Nigerian Certificate in Education (NCE) in subject(s) which are very relevant to YOUR proposed programme of study with a minimum of one merit and two (2) passes.</p>\n\n<p>iii. Likewise, International Baccalaureates, Interim Joint Matriculation Board (IJMB) with at least two &lsquo;A&rsquo; level papers in relevant subjects and prerequisites number of &lsquo;O&rsquo; level credit passes.</p>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements into NOUN For Masters</h3>\n\n<p>1: You are required to have a first degree from a University which MUST be recognised by the Senate of NOUN in a related field of study. (Almost all National Universities Commission (NUC) approved Universities are recognized by NOUN)</p>\n\n<p>2: You are also required to have a postgraduate diploma in a related field from a University which MUST be recognised by Management of NOUN, this would go a long way, in helping you be admitted too.</p>\n\n<p>3: The school senate also accepts a good honours degree in Education (Arts, Languages, Sciences, Social Sciences, Vocational and Technical subjects) from any University which is recognized by NOUN.</p>\n\n<p>4: The Senate also confirms, that holders of HND (with a minimum of Upper Credit) from institutions recognized by the Senate of NOUN, in a related field of study are accepted to come for their Masters in NOUN.</p>\n\n<p>5: Members of relevant professional bodies may apply for the Master of Business (MBA) programme. Relevant professional bodies, includes companies which are recognized, or registered in Nigeria.</p>\n\n<p>We do advice you, if you&rsquo;re going for your MBA programme, you can give the school senate more information about your professional body and they might accept you. The senate of NOUN, has made admission into NOUN as easy as possible.</p>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements into NOUN For PHD</h3>\n\n<p>What is the meaning of PHD? PHD is also known and called doctorate. This is the highest degree which is awarded by a graduate school, and this degree is usually awarded to a person who has completed at least three years of graduate study.</p>\n\n<p>1: Candidates who are going for the Doctor of Philosophy degree programmes, should note, that the school senate has made it mandatory, that all applicants Must possess a masters degree in relevant fields of study from a University which is recognised by the Senate of the NOUN.<br />\nTake note, that you must posses this Master degree with a minimum score average of not less than 60% or a Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) of 3.5 on a 5-point scale.</p>\n\n<p>2: Aspiring candidates who are going for the Ph. D Programmes in NOUN, should take note, that they will be invited for an interactive session with the School of Postgraduate Studies before an offer of admission is made to them.</p>\n\n<p>3: The NOU.org.ng team, also wish to notify and ADVISES all candidates going for admission into NOUN for PHD programmes, that they are to forward the following listed below:</p>\n\n<p>a) Transcripts of their academic records,<br />\nb) Also forward three (3) referees report, and two of these referees must be from persons very well acquainted with the candidate&rsquo;s academic work.</p>\n\n<p>The above required items should be forwarded to the Dean of the School from which admission is requested.</p>\n\n<h4><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE:</strong></h4>\n\n<p>We would also love to notify all candidates, that they may be required to satisfy additional requirements by specific Schools in their location or their school of choice.</p>\n\n<h3>Admission Requirements into NOUN For Other Students/Workers</h3>\n\n<p>This is the admission requirements for 200 LEVEL(For Direct Entry)</p>\n\n<p>1: Applicants should take note, that they must produce their National Diploma from recognised academic institutions.</p>\n\n<p>2: Applicants must also make sure, that they provide their Nigerian Certificate in Education (NCE) in subject(s) which are relevant to the proposed programme of study with a minimum of one merit and two passes.</p>\n\n<p>3: All interested applicants should take note of the International Baccalaureates, Interim Joint Matriculation Board (IJMB) with at least two &lsquo;A&rsquo; level papers in relevant subjects and prerequisites number of &lsquo;O&rsquo; level credit passes.</p>\n\n<p>4: We would also love to inform and notify all interested applicants/candidates seeking for admission into School of Law, that the NOUN senate requires them, to have a minimum of second class (lower) degree from any recognized university with at least five credits including the following subjects:</p>\n\n<p>a) English language,<br />\nb) Literature in English,<br />\nc) A credit pass in Mathematics at not more than two sittings in NECO/SSCE or GCE &lsquo;O&rsquo; level only.</p>\n\n<h3>Guidelines On How to Pay for Noun Admission/Application Form</h3>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Please, ensure that you pay as follows for the NOUN application forms: Undergraduate Programmes which will costs you the sum of N5,000.00(Five thousand naira only)</li>\n	<li>The Postgraduate (PGD and Masters) Programmes application form goes for N7, 500.00 (Seven thousand, five hundred naira Only).</li>\n	<li>While the Doctor of Philosophy (doctorate Degree or Ph.D) Programmes application form is sold for the sum of N10, 000.00 (Ten thousand naira only).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>NOUN OFFICIAL BANKS ACCOUNT NUMBERS</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Bank Name</strong>: First City Monument Bank<br />\n<strong>Account Number</strong>: PLEASE ASK THE CUSTOMER SUPPORT</p>\n\n<p><strong>Bank Name</strong>: Ecobank<br />\n<strong>Account Number</strong>: PLEASE ASK THE CUSTOMER SUPPORT</p>\n\n<p><strong>Bank Name</strong>: Zenith Bank<br />\n<strong>Account Number</strong>: PLEASE ASK THE CUSTOMER SUPPORT</p>\n\n<p><strong>Bank Name</strong>: Skye Bank plc.<br />\n<strong>Account Number</strong>: PLEASE ASK THE CUSTOMER SUPPORT</p>\n\n<h3><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT PAYMENT</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Please, before you make any sort of payment into the above mentioned/listed bank accounts, go to the bank customer care center or support Unit.</p>\n\n<p>Provide them with the bank account number and humbly request them to verify if the account truly belongs to NOUN.</p>\n\n<p>Hope this information helps you immensely, and please, do share this information with your friends on Facebook, Twitter and Google+, using the share buttons below.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\"><strong>For Admission assistance, CLICK HERE</strong></a></p>\n\n<p>Thank You.<br />\nnounloaded!!!.</p>\n', '2023-06-19 15:08:07', '2023-06-19 15:08:07'),
(10, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'NOUN Admission Forms: Price, Portal, Closing Date ', '231906111427000000admission2.jpg', 'noun-admission-forms-price-portal-closing-date', '<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">This is to inform the general public, parents, sponsors and interested applicants that admission forms into the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN, are currently on sale. In this post, you will have access to the application links for the BSC programmes for the 100 and 200-level applicants, and post-graduate programmes for the Masters, P.hD&nbsp; and certificate courses.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Candidates should take note of sections for the eligibility and requirements for admission, methods of payment and more, as well detailed in the post below.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Background of the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) Programme</span></span></strong></span></span></span></span></h3>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">The National Open University of Nigeria is a federal open and distance learning institution, the first of its kind in the West African sub-region. It is Nigeria&#39;s largest tertiary institution in terms of student number and is popularly referred to as &#39;NOUN&#39;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">The university runs its programmes on a part-time i.e distance learning basis. As such, just as the conventional universities, you can have your degree (BSC), and post-graduate certificates at NOUN.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">If you want to know more about NOUN admissions, its certificates and acceptability for jobs, posting of graduates for NYSC, acceptance to the Law School etc, read,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.schoolcontents.info/2018/08/noun-admissions-answers-to-series-of.html\" style=\"color:black; text-decoration:none\" target=\"_blank\">NOUN Admissions: SSCE, Direct Entry, MSC, PGD etc</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">National Open University of Nigeria Admission Requirements Eligibility for Degree (BSC) and Postgraduate Programmes (Masters, PhD</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">)<strong>&nbsp;etc</strong></span></span></span></span></span></span></h3>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Undergraduate Programmes</span></span></strong></span></span></span></span></h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">An applicant for undergraduate admission into NOUN is normally expected to have a minimum of 5 O-level credits including English Language and Mathematics. in not more than two sittings.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Additional requirements might apply for some programmes and these can be viewed after selecting the Programme and entry-level at the Faculty&rsquo;s admission page. The links to each programme and the requirements will be given in the next section.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">JAMB UTME registration or result is not required for admission into the National Open University of Nigeria.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Candidates seeking 200-level admissions should be holders of BSC, HND, ND, NCE, RN, RM, and similar other health-related diplomas and certificates.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:18.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">Postgraduate Programmes</span></span></strong></span></span></span></span></h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">To qualify for admission into any of the postgraduate programmes of the University, a candidate must meet, among others, all matriculation requirements of at least five (5) credit passes including English Language and Mathematics. Some programmes accept at least a pass in Mathematics.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">For Postgraduate Diploma Programmes, Candidates must possess either a minimum of pass Bachelors Degree in any discipline from a University recognised by the Senate of the NOUN OR a Higher National Diploma with a minimum of Lower Credit. For the Postgraduate Diploma in Legislative Drafting, the candidate must have been called to the Bar. Also for admission into the school of Business and Human Resource Management Postgraduate Diploma programmes, candidates with professional qualifications such as ACA, ACIS, ACIB, ACII, ACIA, etc may be considered on individual merit.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">For Master&#39;s degree programmes, candidates must possess either a bachelor&#39;s degree with a minimum of second class lower in the relevant field of study from a University recognised by the Senate of the NOUN. However, holders of lower classification and with a minimum of 2 years of relevant post-qualification experience may be considered on individual merit OR a Postgraduate Diploma in a related field of study from a recognised University OR A Higher National Diploma with a minimum of Upper Credit in the relevant field of study. Candidates with membership certificates of relevant professional bodies may apply for the Master of Business (MBA) programme.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">For the Doctor of Philosophy Degree programmes, candidates must possess a Master&#39;s degree in the relevant field of study from a University recognised by the Senate of the NOUN with a minimum score average of not less than 60% or a cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) of 3.5 on a 5-point scale.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\">National Open University of Nigeria Method of Application and Payment</span></span></strong></span></span></span></span></h3>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Visit the NOUN admission portal or just click <a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/posts/noun-admission-requirements\">https://www.nouonline.net/</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">On the page, locate &quot;<strong>Apply for Admission</strong>&quot;.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">This will open available applications, click on the one you&#39;re proposing e.g <a href=\"https://www.admissions.nouonline.net/zzappl_ugrad.php\" style=\"color:black; text-decoration:none\" target=\"_blank\">undergraduate programme</a>, <a href=\"https://www.admissions.nouonline.net/zzpappl_pgrad.php\" style=\"color:black; text-decoration:none\" target=\"_blank\">Postgraduate</a>, <a href=\"https://www.admissions.nouonline.net/zzpappl_phd.php\" style=\"color:black; text-decoration:none\" target=\"_blank\">PhD</a> etc. Click on each of the links for the right application</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">To apply for a programme, select the Faculty, and choose the programme and entry-level so that the View Requirement button is enabled. Clicking this button will reveal the corresponding entry requirement and enable the Apply button on the pre-payment application page.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Fill in all the remaining details on the page before submitting.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">On successful submission of the pre-payment form, you are redirected to Remita to obtain an RRR invoice which should be used to effect payment for the application form.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">An applicant who pays online using a payment card will automatically obtain the online form which must be filled out before submission.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Applicants who pay through a bank branch must click on Continue after payment... and enter their Unique ID and RRR. They are also given the opportunity to change the Programme applied for.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">Applicants who had paid using an RRR generated last semester or earlier must restart the application process up to the point when they are re-directed to Remita. They should now use the newly generated UniqueID with the old RRR used for payment when they click Proceed after payment.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">In all cases, a successful payment will lead to the generation of an online application form which should be filled out before submission online. The admission process is automated and the outcome is virtually instantaneous!</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#2e2e2e\">For NOUN Admission assistance, <a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\">CLICK HERE</a></span></span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>\n', '2023-06-19 15:14:27', '2023-06-19 15:14:27');
