(11, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'National Open University of Nigeria NOUN 2023/2024 Admission Application and Registration Form Out', '231906111847000000admission.png', 'national-open-university-of-nigeria-noun-20232024-admission-application-and-registration-form-out', '<p>THE National Open University of Nigeria Management, has released the admission application and registration form for 2023/2024 Admission.</p>\n\n<p>Using this medium, we wish to inform and notify the general public, most especially, all persons, parents, guardians, friends or candidates who are interested or know of anyone who have interested of studying in NOUN, that the school board has released the 2023 Registration form and they can now apply.</p>\n\n<p>Just in case you&rsquo;re disturbed and don&rsquo;t know how the lists of courses supported in the academic institution, don&rsquo;t worry, because we also have the full and complete list&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>!</p>\n\n<p>We are really happy to bring this information to all aspirants, that the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/posts/noun-admission-requirements\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">National Open University of Nigeria</a>&nbsp;(NOUN) Application Form for the 2023/2024 Admission is currently ongoing.</p>\n\n<p>All interested persons should take note that the sales of&nbsp;NOUN Admission form for the 2022 admission&nbsp;which was recently announced by the administration of the National Open University Academic Institution.</p>\n\n<p>So therefore, since you are now aware that the National Open University of Nigeria Application form for the 2022/2023 Admission is currently ongoing, all interested and qualified candidates should read through the procedures which are required from all students.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Available Programmes at National Open University of Nigeria, NOUN</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Listing the full available programmes, which are accredited by the National University Commission (NUC) of Nigeria, including the post graduate and graduate courses, would take a lot of space here.</p>\n\n<p>But we have provided here, a reference to where you can check the lists of all courses which are available and accredited by NUC.</p>\n\n<p>The next guideline for getting admitted into the&nbsp;<strong>National Open University of Nigeria, NOUN,</strong>&nbsp;is by purchasing the school&rsquo;s registration or application form.</p>\n\n<p>The sale of noun application form is announced by the school Admission board.</p>\n\n<p>The academic institution announces the sales of application form for admission into the following programmes which are listed below:</p>\n\n<p>* Certificate,<br />\n* Diploma,<br />\n* Undergraduate,<br />\n* Post Graduate Diploma,<br />\n* Masters Degree, and<br />\n* Doctor of Philosophy Programmes for 2023 Academic Session.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>For the full details on the application form,&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">CLICK HERE</a></strong>&nbsp;TO DOWNLOAD THE FORM, which includes all admission advert, plus the following:</p>\n\n<p>All available programmes,<br />\nDuration of each programmes,<br />\n<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Admission requirements</a>,<br />\nHow To Apply<br />\nMethod of Application.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Step By Step Procedures On How To Apply for NOUN Admission 2023/2024 (E-APPLICATION) Through Internet</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Take note that registration is done exclusively online, you don&rsquo;t need to visit any of the school&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.nounportal.org/noun-list-of-study-centres-and-their-office-address-in-nigeria/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">study centres</a>&nbsp;before you&rsquo;re fully admitted. Follow the guidelines below to commence your application.</p>\n\n<p>One of the main reasons for the creation of nounportal.org is because of the stress aspirants and applicants pass through before they secure admission into the school. Our main aim is to provide you and guide you throughout the registration path till you&rsquo;re fully registered.</p>\n\n<p>One of our purposes, is providing you with procedures on how to apply for NOUN Admission.</p>\n\n<p>Please do take note that applying for Admission into the National Open University of Nigeria is done entirely on the internet (online) through the school portal, which is open 24 hours and operates 7 days throughout the year. This is to say, that you can register for admission into NOUN, anytime and anywhere.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>What to Do Before Filling NOUN Application Form</strong></h3>\n\n<p>Before filling the NOUN application form, you are required to pay a registration fee. Take note that filling the National Open University Admission Application form is done online, but before that, here&rsquo;s how to pay the registration and application forms.</p>\n\n<p>(Take note that both the registration and application forms are the same)</p>\n\n<p>Guide : There are selected few commercial banks which are in partnership with NOUN, here are the lists of these approved banks. You&rsquo;re required to visit any of the following Approved Banks.</p>\n\n<table>\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<td>\n			<h3><strong>Names of BANKS</strong></h3>\n			</td>\n			<td>\n			<h3><strong>ACCOUNT NUMBERS</strong></h3>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>First City Monument Bank</td>\n			<td>MEET the customer support and ask for the Official account of NOUN</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Ecobank Plc</td>\n			<td>MEET the customer support and ask for the Official account of NOUN</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Zenith Bank</td>\n			<td>MEET the customer support and ask for the Official account of NOUN</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Skye Bank</td>\n			<td>MEET the customer support and ask for the Official account of NOUN</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>IMPORTANT NOTE</strong></p>\n\n<p>There are some security measures you&rsquo;re expected to take note of, before making payment. Be informed that the school won&rsquo;t in any way, be held reliable for any payment made into any account other than the above designated banks and account numbers which are listed below.<br />\nBefore making payment, walk to the banks customer support, ask them to verify the account number if it truly belongs to the National Open University of Nigeria.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 2:</strong>&nbsp;You should pay the following fees for NOUN application forms, each programmes have their own applicable fees:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guide 3:</strong>&nbsp;When you want to pay the above stipulated fee, Ensure, please MAKE SURE that you ask the customer support specifically for a&nbsp;<strong>NOUN Teller</strong>, which is specially designed for NOUN registration payment.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 4:</strong>&nbsp;After you&rsquo;ve successfully made the payment, please proceed and collect the Application pin CODE which is always equivalent to the amount paid for your form from the Bank.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 5</strong>: When you&rsquo;ve completed the above steps and procedures, it&rsquo;s time for the main registration. You are required to visit the website of National Open University Nigeria here &ndash;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.noun.edu.ng</a>&nbsp;and click on the title which says: &ldquo;Application Form&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 6</strong>: When the application form webpage loads up on your browser, proceed and use your Application PIN to access your own personalixed NOUN online application form.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 7:</strong>&nbsp;Here is where you are expected to fill the registration form with the required details. Proceed and complete the online NOUN admission application form by providing all the required data/information correctly.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 8</strong>: After you have successfully completed the registration form, take note that you can easily navigate around and edit the form as many times as possible, before you submit it.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 9</strong>: When you have checked the form and see that everything is correct, then you can submit the application form by clicking on the&nbsp;<strong>Submit Button</strong>&nbsp;at the bottom of the displayed screen.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Guides 10</strong>: When you&rsquo;re done, you can then proceed and print out your provisional admission letter.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Important Notes</strong></p>\n\n<p>All candidates who are interested in applying for the&nbsp;<strong>2023/2024 National Open University of Nigeria admission</strong>&nbsp;should make sure, that they always insist on paying the stipulated cost only in the bank and obtain official receipt at the point of payment. This will be your proof of payment.</p>\n\n<p>Just in case you want to know the current location of NOUN Study Centres officially approved by the school management, including all study centres Addresses and Emails &rarr;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>&nbsp;CLICK HERE</strong></a>&nbsp;to see the list</p>\n\n<p><strong>NOUN Admission Registration and Application Form Closing Date:</strong></p>\n\n<p>As at the time of publishing this article, the institution&rsquo;s admission board is yet to announce the application closing date.</p>\n\n<p>But one thing is sure, which is the application Form for the 2023 NOUN admission is still ongoing. We are still waiting for the varsity&rsquo;s board to announce the registration closing date.</p>\n\n<p>However, we&rsquo;ll advice you, to take huge advantage of this and apply right now. Just in case you are not aware, the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) is the 21<sup>st</sup>&nbsp;most preferred and BEST educational institution in Nigeria.</p>\n\n<p>Please share this information with your friends on facebook, Twitter and Google+, using the share buttons below.</p>\n', '2023-06-19 15:18:47', '2023-06-19 15:18:47'),
(12, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'NOUN Admission Form 2023/2024 | Diploma, Degree & PG', '231906112629000000admission.png', 'noun-admission-form-20232024-diploma-degree-pg', '<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) admission form for certificate, diploma, undergraduate and postgraduate programmes&nbsp;.</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The management of the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) is now selling application forms for admission into its Certificate, Diploma, Undergraduate and postgraduate programmes for the 2023/2024 academic session.&nbsp;</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Applications are hereby invited from suitably qualified candidates for admission into the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) Certificate, Diploma, Undergraduates, Postgraduate Diploma, Masters Degree and Doctor Of Philosophy (Ph.D) Programmes.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><em>NOUN</em> operates a flexible mode of study which allows a student to determine the pace, place, time and medium of study. Students&rsquo; support facilities are available at all our Study Centres nationwide.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><strong>NOUN Admission Requirements for All Programmes</strong></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">1. Certificate Programmes</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">a) Proficiency Certificate Programmes</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">No previous experience or qualification is necessary.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Ability to read and write will be an advantage.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Note: Candidates for Proficiency Certificates will NOT be qualified to proceed to Certificates/Diploma programmes without possessing the requisite basic qualifications.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">b) University (Academic) Certificate Programmes</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Junior Secondary School Certificate.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Minimum of 2 credits in SSCE/GCE &lsquo;O&rsquo; Level, NECO, NABTEB and at not more than two sittings.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">T.C II with at least 2 merits at not more than two sittings.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Mature candidates of 30 years and above with relevant work experience of not less than 10 years or evidence of prior knowledge/proficiency in a relevant field may be considered on their merit.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">I&rsquo;dadiyah Certificate of Standard Islamiyyah School.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">2. Diploma Programmes</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A minimum of three credits in SSCE/GCE &lsquo;O&rsquo; Level, NECO and NABTEB at not more than two sittings with at least a pass in English Language.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A minimum of three merits in Teacher Grade II Certificate at not more than two sittings.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Senior Islamic School Certificate/Higher Islamiyyah Certificate including Arabic and Islamic Studies</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Thanawiyyah Certificate of Standard Islamiyyah School.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">NOUN Academic Certificate and Certificates of other recognized institutions.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Note: To qualify to proceed to appropriate degree programme of NOUN, holders of Diploma Certificates would be required to make up any deficiencies in their SSCE/GCE, NECO, NABTEB and T.C II.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">3. Undergraduate Programmes.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">100 Level:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Five credits in the SSCE / GCE O&rsquo;Level / NECO / NABTEB or&nbsp;equivalents at not more than two (2) sittings obtained in&nbsp;subjects relevant to the proposed field(s) of study.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Teachers&rsquo; Grade II Certificates with a minimum of five&nbsp;merits or its combination with any of the certificates listed&nbsp;under (i) to obtain equivalent of five credits at &lsquo;O&rsquo;Levels.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates seeking admission into School of Law must&nbsp;have five(5) credits including English Language, Literature&nbsp;in English and at least a credit Pass in Mathematics at not&nbsp;more than two (2) sittings in NECO / SSCE or GCE O/L&nbsp;only.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The School of Arts and Social Sciences requires that one&nbsp;of the five credits or merits must be in English Language,&nbsp;while at least two (2) should be in subjects relevant to the&nbsp;proposed field.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">For School of Management Sciences, the credit passes at&nbsp;Ordinary Level must include English and Mathematics</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">For School of Education, the credit passes must include&nbsp;Mathematics for Science Education and English Language&nbsp;for all humanities. Additionally, those in Science Education&nbsp;must have credit in English Language.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">For School of Science and Technology, the credit passes&nbsp;must include Mathematics and English Language.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The minimum entry requirement for B.Sc. Environmental&nbsp;Science and Resource Management is five (5) O&rsquo;Level&nbsp;(SSCE / NECO / GCE or NABTEB) Credits at not more than&nbsp;two sittings including English Language and Mathematics&nbsp;and any of Geography, Physics, Chemistry, Biology,&nbsp;Agricultural Science and Economics.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">200 Level:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">National Diploma at Upper Credit from recognised&nbsp;institutions.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">National Certificate in Education (NCE) in subject(s)&nbsp;relevant to the proposed programme of study with a&nbsp;minimum of one merit and two passes.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">International Baccalaureates, Interim Joint Matriculation&nbsp;Board (IJMB) with at least two &lsquo;A&rsquo; Level papers in relevant&nbsp;subjects and pre-requisite number of &lsquo;O&rsquo; Level credit&nbsp;passes.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates for entry into School of Law must have a&nbsp;minimum of Second Class (Lower) degree from any&nbsp;recognized University with at least five credits including&nbsp;English Language, Literature in English and a credit pass in&nbsp;Mathematics at not more than two sittings in NECO / SCCE&nbsp;or GCE &lsquo;O&rsquo; Level only.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates for entry into School of Science &amp; Technology&nbsp;may be admitted into 300 Level of the programme provided&nbsp;they have the following qualification:<br />\n	a) Five (5) credit pass in not more than two sittings in&nbsp;SSCE / NECO / GCE or NABTEB in the following&nbsp;subjects: English Geography and Economics.<br />\n	b) A registered and licensed Community Health&nbsp;Extension Worker with a Diploma in Community&nbsp;Health Officers Programme (Higher National&nbsp;Diploma) and with not less than two years post&nbsp;qualification experience.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Other Requirements:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Five (5) &lsquo;0&rsquo; level credit passes and &lsquo;A&rsquo; level passes must be in subjects relevant to the proposed programme (s).</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">&lsquo;O&rsquo; level credit pass in Mathematics is required for all Sciences and Technology, Business Education and Science Education Programmes. &lsquo;O&rsquo; level pass in Mathematics may be considered for Social Sciences Programmes. Also, &lsquo;O&rsquo; level pass in English Language may be considered for Physics and Mathematics Programmes.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates applying for B.A English, B.A. (Ed) English and B.Sc. Mass Communication must have &lsquo;O&rsquo; level credit pass in Literature in English.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Holders of First Degree, HND or RN with prior knowledge and relevant work experience may be considered for advanced placement and waiver.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates awaiting results of any relevant examination may also apply; they should however note that processing of application will not be completed until entry requirements are met.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">4. POSTGRADUATE DIPLOMA PROGRAMMES</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates seeking admission must possess either Bachelor Degree Certificates or equivalent from institutions recognised by the Senate of NOUN; or</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Holders of HND with a minimum of Lower Credit from institutions recognised by the Senate of NOUN.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates seeking admission into the School of Law must possess a minimum of L.L.B degree.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">candidate seeking admission for PGD Agricultural Extension and Management must possess a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree with at least 3<sup>rd</sup> class division is required. Candidates with pass degree and minimum of 3 years related experience may be accepted. HND holders in Agric Science or other related disciplines may be admitted. Holders of Bachelor degree in basic Science, Biological/Earth Sciences, and Agricultural Sciences from Universities that are recognised by NOUN are admitable.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">candidate seeking admission for the PGD HIV/AIDS Education and Management must possess HND or a good first degree in related field of study. In addition, 5 credits in English, Mathematics, a science subject and 2 other subjects.</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">5. MASTERS DEGREE PROGRAMMES</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A first degree with a minimum of Second Class Lower from a University recognised by the Senate of NOUN in a related field or study.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A postgraduate diploma in a related field from a University recognised by Senate may also be admitted.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">A good honours degree in Education (Arts, Languages, Sciences, Social Sciences, Vocational and Technical subjects) from any University recognized by the Senate of NOUN.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Prospective students seeking admission for M.Sc. HIV/AIDS Management are required to have PGD in HIV/AIDS education and management as well as 5 credits in: English and Mathematics, a science subject and 2 other subjects.</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">6. DOCTOR OF PHILOSOPHY (PH.D) PROGRAMMES</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">For the Doctor of Philosophy degree programmes, candidates must possess a masters degree in relevant fields of study from a University recognised by the Senate of the NOUN with a minimum score average of not less than 60% or a Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) of 3.5 on a 5-point scale.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates for Ph.D Programmes will be invited for an interactive session before an offer of admission is made.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Candidates are advised to forward transcripts of their academic records and three (3) referees report, 2 of which must be from persons very well acquainted with the candidate&rsquo;s academic work, to the Dean, Postgraduate School from which admission is requested.</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">7. ACCESS PROGRAMME.</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">As part of her mandate to increase access to Higher Education, the&nbsp;National Open University of Nigeria now offers a Remedial&nbsp;Programme at &lsquo;O&rsquo; level to the Nigerian Public.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Students who are admitted into these programmes will be taught&nbsp;through the face-to-face mode for a full academic year after which&nbsp;they would sit for any National &lsquo;O&rsquo; Level examinations of their&nbsp;choice</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">For a start, the programme would take off in three Study Centres of&nbsp;the University: Lagos, Kaduna and Kebbi respectively.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:18pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><strong>How to Apply for NOUN Admission Form</strong></span></span></h2>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">The entire process is electronic and online for 24-hours a day. The method of application is as follows:</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visit the sitehttps: <a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\">//www.nouonline.net/</a></span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">On the Home Page, go to the Menu Bar, Click on Apply for Admission</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Select either Undergraduate Programme/Postgraduate Programme/PhD Programme/ACETEL Programmes</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Goto &ldquo;Choose Faculty&rdquo; (note it can be found at the left hand side of the screen)</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Select Faculty</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Fill displayed form</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click below to view admission criteria</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click &ldquo;Apply&rdquo; to proceed.</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Take note of the UNIQUE ID displayed</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click &lsquo;Continue&rsquo; button</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Select Bank Branch as payment type</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click &ldquo;Pay&rdquo;</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Copy and take your RRR number to any bank branch for payment.</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">After payment</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Perform step 1 to 3</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Goto &ldquo;Continue After Payment&rdquo;</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Input Unique ID, RRR number and Programme</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click &ldquo;Proceed&rdquo;</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Fill Form. Note: all fields marked with red star are compulsory.</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">After filling form</span></span></p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Click &ldquo;Submit&rdquo;</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Print Admission Letter</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Visit the nearest study centre for screening</span></span></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Applicants are advised to insist on paying the stipulated cost only and obtain official receipt at the point of payment.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Pay as follow for NOUN online application forms:</span></span></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Undergraduate Programmes N5, 000.00 (five thousand naira only)</span></span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Postgraduate (PGD and Masters) Programmes N7, 500.00 (Seven thousand five hundred naira only).</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D) Programmes N10,000.00 (Ten Thousand Naira only).</span></span></p>\n', '2023-06-19 15:26:29', '2023-06-19 15:26:29');
INSERT INTO `blog_posts` (`id`, `ref_id`, `ref_role`, `ref_email`, `post_catid`, `post_category`, `post_title`, `post_imgurl`, `post_url`, `post_desc`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(13, '1', 'admin', 'admin@nounloaded.com.ng', '9', 'NOUN Admission ', 'How To Apply For NOUN Admission 2023/2024', '231906113619000000admission2.jpg', 'how-to-apply-for-noun-admission-20232024', '<p><strong>&ndash; National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) Admission Form and Requirements</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&ndash; NOUN Admission Form for SSCE, Diploma, Undergraduate, Masters, Postgraduate and Phd Degree Programme</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>&ndash; NOUN Admission Procedure For 2023_1 Academic Session</strong></p>\n\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\">National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN)</a>&nbsp;is excited to announce that the admission form for the 2023_1 academic session is now available for purchase. This is a fantastic opportunity for those who are looking to further their education and take the next step in their academic journey.</p>\n\n<p>NOUN offers a wide range of courses to choose from, including certificates, diplomas, undergraduate, postgraduate diplomas, master&rsquo;s degrees and even a Doctor of Philosophy (Ph.D) program. So, whether you&rsquo;re just starting out or looking to advance your career, NOUN has something for everyone.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2>Brief Intro About The National Open University of Nigeria</h2>\n\n<p>The National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) is a leading institution of distance learning in Africa. Established in 1983, NOUN provides access to quality education for individuals who are unable to attend traditional universities due to work or family obligations.</p>\n\n<p>The university offers a wide range of undergraduate and postgraduate programs in diverse fields such as Law, Art, Health Science, Education, Management, Social Sciences and Sciences.</p>\n\n<p>One of the unique features of NOUN is its use of modern technology to deliver course materials to students. The university has a state-of-the-art e-library and provides students with access to online resources, including video lectures and interactive quizzes.</p>\n\n<p>The university is also noted for its flexibility and affordability. Students can enroll at any time and study at their own pace, making it an ideal option for working professionals. Additionally, NOUN&rsquo;s tuition fees are significantly lower than those of traditional universities in Nigeria.</p>\n\n<p>NOUN is an excellent choice for anyone looking to further their education while balancing other responsibilities. With its cutting-edge technology, flexible study options, and affordable tuition, NOUN is well-positioned to help students achieve their academic and career goals.</p>\n\n<h2>Mode of Study in NOUN</h2>\n\n<p>i.&nbsp;<strong><u>Academic Sessions</u></strong>: NOUN runs on a full-term basis with flexible terms. Flexible in the sense that individuals are allowed to progress at own will&rsquo;s pace. In order words, students are free to choose how they progress in their academic curriculum. The institution is semester oriented rather than session.</p>\n\n<p>ii.&nbsp;<strong><u>Student Portal</u></strong>: This is a more or less the students&rsquo; dashboard where every activity&nbsp;as regards registrations is carried out. Such registration includes generation of RRR, payment of school fees, registration of courses and exams, printing of I.D card, as well as&nbsp;checking of results and submission of tutor marked assignments. Academic histories and exam results are also stored on the portal.</p>\n\n<p>iii.&nbsp;<strong><u>Facilitation</u></strong>: This is a kind of lectures carried out by the lecturers of the university for students in 100 and 900 levels. It is not compulsory but vital for all the students. It is geared towards intimating the students with their course materials. It is however not a criterion for doing well academically as far as NOUN is concerned. Extensive reading of the course materials is. This is because&nbsp;the facilitation is always for a very short period in a given semester and the facilitators hardly touch half of the course materials. The facilitators are not the ones that set the exam question, as questions are sent directly from the headquarters and according to the content of the course material.</p>\n\n<p>iv.&nbsp;<strong><u>Tutor-Marked Assignment (TMA)</u></strong>&nbsp;The tutor-marked assignment is part of the academic curriculum in the National Open University of Nigeria. It is an online based test which is geared towards helping in developing regular study habits in students and give students practice in writing responses to questions thereby having a kind of rehearsal in the preparation for the final examination especially in 100 and 200 levels. It, however, carries 30% of the total grade of any course.</p>\n\n<p>v.&nbsp;<strong><u>Course Materials</u></strong>: Every course in NOUN has its own material both in print and electronic copies. These are lecture-like books designed in such a way to represent the classroom lectures. They are written in units and grouped in modules. The books are not sold separately but are distributed according to the courses registered by the students. The print copies are, however, subject to first come first serve basis and when they are exhausted in a given semester, students are then referred to the electronic copies online.</p>\n\n<p><strong><u>Examinations</u></strong>: NOUN&rsquo;s exams are in two forms, e-exam and pen on paper (POP). The e-exam is for 100 and 200 level courses while the POP is for 300 level and above. All law courses are POP.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Before you start NOUN admission application process, click on the link below to see the updated list of courses offered at the National Open University of Nigeria.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>NOTE:- NOUN Admission, Course and Exam Registration for 2023_1 semester will close on 3rd March 2023</strong></p>\n\n<h2>NOUN ADMISSION REQUIREMENTS</h2>\n\n<p><strong>GENERAL REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n\n<p>1.&nbsp;<strong>An applicant for undergraduate admission</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>An applicant for undergraduate admission into NOUN is normally expected to have a minimum of 5 o-level credits including English Language and Mathematics.</li>\n	<li>Additional requirements might apply for some programmes and these can be viewed after selecting the Programme and entry-level at the Faculty&rsquo;s admission page.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>2.&nbsp;<strong>An applicant for postgraduate admission</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>An applicant for postgraduate admission into NOUN is normally expected to have a minimum of a first degree ( second class lower) for masters or HND for PGD in a related field in addition to 5 O-Level credits including English Language and Mathematics.</li>\n	<li>Additional requirements might apply for some programmes and these can be viewed after selecting the Programme and entry level at the Faculty&rsquo;s admission page.\n	<p>3.&nbsp;<strong>An applicant for Ph.D Programme</strong></p>\n	</li>\n	<li>Candidates must possess a good Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant discipline from the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) or any university recognised by the Senate of NOUN, with a CGPA not below 4.00 on a 5.00 scale. Some Departments may seek higher CGPA, while all Ph.D. candidates will be subjected to oral/written interviews.</li>\n	<li>Also, candidates with a CGPA not below 3.50 on a 5.00 scale can apply for PhD/MPhil admission. They must possess a good Master&rsquo;s degree in a relevant discipline from the National Open University of Nigeria (NOUN) or any university recognised by the Senate of NOUN. Candidates will be subjected to oral/written interviews.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>How Much is the National Open University of Nigeria Admission Form?</h2>\n\n<p>The NOUN admission form is 5,000 Naira for the Undergraduate Programme, the Postgraduate Admission form is 7,500 Naira while PhD admission form is 10,000 Naira<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h2>HOW TO APPLY FOR NATIONAL OPEN UNIVERSITY OF NIGERIA NOUN ADMISSION FORM</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>The first thing you need to do is to open your web browser e.g Opera Mini, Uc Web Or Chrome, and Visit the National open university for Nigeria admission portal&nbsp;https://www.nouonline.net/index.php<strong><a href=\"http://nouedu.net/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;</a></strong>&nbsp;<em><strong>NOTE:- Make use of google chrome browser&nbsp;for easy&nbsp;access</strong></em></li>\n	<li>On the&nbsp;<strong>NOUN</strong>&nbsp;website home page, you will see different menu options. Click on&nbsp;<strong>ADMISSION</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/National-Open-University-NOUN-Admission-Portal-Home-Page.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/National-Open-University-NOUN-Admission-Portal-Home-Page.png\" style=\"height:255px; width:1091px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Click on&nbsp;<strong>APPLY</strong>&nbsp;Select either to&nbsp;<strong>Apply for NOUN Undergraduate Programme</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>NOUN Postgraduate Admission</strong>&nbsp;or a&nbsp;<strong>PhD Programme</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Portal-for-Undergraduate-Postgraduate-and-PHD-Form.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Portal-for-Undergraduate-Postgraduate-and-PHD-Form.png\" style=\"height:190px; width:639px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>After you have chosen your&nbsp;<strong>Programme</strong>, Click on&nbsp;<strong>Choose Faculty (note it can be found at the left-hand side of the NOUN Application page)</strong></li>\n	<li>Now select your F<strong>aculty&nbsp;<em>(Select one of the Faculty from the list of Faculty available e.g NOUN Faculty of Agriculture, Faculty of Arts, Faculty Of Education, Faculty of Health Sciences, Faculty Of LAW, Faculty Of Management Sciences, Faculty of Sciences, Faculty of Social Sciences)</em></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Faculties.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Faculties.png\" style=\"height:527px; width:943px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Choose&nbsp;<strong>programme of Study</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Programme-Application-Page.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Programme-Application-Page.png\" style=\"height:465px; width:435px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Select&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Level&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;View subject required&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;to view compulsory subjects required for&nbsp;<strong>NOUN admission into BNSc Nursing&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(Note: I am using Nursing as an example don&rsquo;t go and fill it oh)</strong></em></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Application-Page-for-Nursing-Programme.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Application-Page-for-Nursing-Programme.png\" style=\"height:315px; width:528px\" /></a></p>\n\n<p>These are the subject requirements of Nursing programme:</p>\n\n<h3>ADMISSION REQUIREMENTS<br />\nBNSC NURSING<br />\nENTRY LEVEL: 100</h3>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<h4><strong>ADMISSION REQUIREMENTS</strong><br />\n<strong>B.NSC. NURSING (NEW)</strong><br />\n<strong>ENTRY LEVEL: 100</strong></h4>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<hr />\n<table id=\"reqsub\">\n	<tbody>\n		<tr>\n			<th colspan=\"2\">\n			<p>COMPULSORY O-LEVEL REQUIREMENTS</p>\n			</th>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\n			<p>Credit passes in&nbsp;<strong>five</strong>&nbsp;subjects which&nbsp;<strong>must&nbsp;</strong>include the following:</p>\n			</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Subject</td>\n			<td>Min Grade</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Biology</td>\n			<td>C6</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Chemistry</td>\n			<td>C6</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>English Language</td>\n			<td>C6</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Mathematics</td>\n			<td>C6</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Physics</td>\n			<td>C6</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<th colspan=\"2\">\n			<p>PRACTICE LICENSE</p>\n			</th>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Registered Midwifery</td>\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\n		</tr>\n		<tr>\n			<td>Registered Nurse (rn)</td>\n		</tr>\n	</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Now Click&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Apply&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;to proceed to payment.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>NOTE:- NOUN Undergraduate Admission Form is five thousand naira (#5,000), Postgraduate Admission Form is seven thousand five hundred naira (#7,500)</strong></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<p><em><strong>Here is the type of message that will appear on your screen: You have chosen to apply for BNSc Nursing in the Faculty of Health Sciences. The application fee for this programme is N5,000.00 (Five Thousand Naira Only)</strong></em></p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Proceed</strong>&nbsp;and Input details on the newly opened portal page</li>\n	<li>Choose&nbsp;<strong>Bank branch</strong>&nbsp;as payment type and&nbsp;<strong>Click Pay</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://nounitesportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/07-Pay-Noun-Admission-fee-with-remita-nigeria-1.png\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img alt=\"Pay-Noun-Admission-fee-with-remita-nigeria 1\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/07-Pay-Noun-Admission-fee-with-remita-nigeria-1.png\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Copy and take the RRR number to any bank branch for payment</li>\n	<li>You can also pay online through&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.remita.net/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">remita.net</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>AFTER PAYMENT</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Perform&nbsp;<strong>1st Step, 2nd Step, 3rd Step above</strong></li>\n	<li>After performing step 1-3, Click on&nbsp;<strong>Continue after payment</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Form-Payment-Page.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Form-Payment-Page.png\" style=\"height:198px; width:829px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Input&nbsp;<a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/\">RRR Number,&nbsp;</a>Select Programme, Level and Click Proceed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Application-Payment-Page.png\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://edusportal.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/NOUN-Admission-Application-Payment-Page.png\" style=\"height:506px; width:421px\" /></a></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Fill the NOUN Admission Form</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>AFTER FILLING FORM</h2>\n\n<p>1.&nbsp;Click&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;Submit&rdquo;</strong></p>\n\n<p>2.&nbsp;Print your&nbsp;NOUN Provisional Admission Letter and the admission form</p>\n\n<p>3. Upload your document to NOUN portal</p>\n\n<p>3.&nbsp;Visit&nbsp;the&nbsp;the study centre you choose during registration for your screening.</p>\n\n<p><strong>If you need help, NOUNLOADED TEAM can help you to process your Admission and upload of credentials kindly contact us.&nbsp; </strong><a href=\"http://nounloaded.com.ng/our-services\"><strong>CLICK HERE TO SEE OUR SERVICES</strong></a></p>\n\n<h2>Required Documents For NOUN Admission Screening</h2>\n\n<p>The documents required during NOUN admission screening for New student&rsquo;s clearance are the ORIGINAL and THREE photocopies of the following items:</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>NOUN Admission letter</li>\n	<li>Proof of ALL REQUIRED payments, such as deposit slips and/or a comprehensive printout of all expected payments. (right from the basic form of money, i.e N5,000 to the most recent payment, either normal&nbsp;school fees&nbsp;and/or course registration fees)</li>\n	<li>O&rsquo;level certificate (Original and photocopy)</li>\n	<li>Birth certificate or sworn affidavit (not less than 5 years ago)</li>\n	<li>Passport Photograph (not more than 3 months)</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>NOUN ADMISSION FAQ</h2>\n\n<p><strong>NOUN Admission List 2023</strong></p>\n\n<p>As of now, The National Open University of Nigeria doesn&rsquo;t have a separate Page or Portal for checking of students (NOUN Admission List). So disregard any media disclosing the List of NOUN Admission List or something similar, and do report to us if you can.</p>\n\n<h2>What to do after being Admitted into NOUN</h2>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Signup at the&nbsp;Nouonline.Net&nbsp;Portal with your student credentials (Matric Number and Password)</li>\n	<li>Print admission letters</li>\n	<li>Update&nbsp;nouonline&nbsp;profile with a recent passport photograph&nbsp;<strong>(How To Upload Your Picture To National Open University Of Nigeria (NOUONLINE) Portal)</strong></li>\n	<li>Print your student Identity card (ID Card) (<strong>How To Print National Open University Of Nigeria NOUN Student ID Card</strong>)</li>\n	<li>Pay NOUN SCHOOL fee, Course registrations and exam fees.</li>\n	<li>Review&nbsp;Noun registrable courses&nbsp;and Register courses for examination.</li>\n	<li>Track all noun student&rsquo;s programmes and activities&nbsp;to know what to expect each week or month and follow up accordingly.</li>\n	<li>Download noun course materials PDF&nbsp;for your registered courses.</li>\n	<li>Get prepared for the&nbsp;noun tutor-marked assignments (TMAs) exercise.</li>\n	<li>Check&nbsp;NOUN TMA Timetable&nbsp;updates</li>\n	<li>Get&nbsp;NOUN exam past questions&nbsp;when necessary</li>\n</ul>\n', '2023-06-19 15:36:19', '2023-06-19 15:36:19'),
